18/07/2006
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- The EU foreign ministers approved the launch of bilateral dialogue with Montenegro on Monday (17 July), now that all EU member states have recognised Montenegro as an independent and sovereign state. The ministers are holding a two-day meeting of the EU Council in Brussels. They called on Podgorica to align its stances with those of the EU in areas relating to foreign policy and security issues. (Vijesti, Pobjeda - 18/07/06; EU Web site - 17/07/06)
